  "description": "This dataset comprises EEG recordings from 40 participants performing a two-door decision-making task with probabilistic feedback. Participants selected between doors in blocks of 20 trials, receiving monetary gains or losses. The experiment manipulated learning conditions by contrasting learnable blocks (60% vs. 10% win probabilities) with unlearnable blocks (random outcomes matched to learnable block statistics). Post-block surveys assessed subjective perceptions of door quality, enjoyment, motivation, and performance.",
